## Why Is This Good?

### 🔒 Security
- **Attackers can't directly reach databases** - they're hidden
- **Compromising one layer doesn't expose others** - if an app server is hacked, the database is still safe
- **Every connection is logged** - you know exactly who talked to who

### 📈 Scalability
- **Easy to add more servers** - just change a number in the code
- **Works across 2 data centers (AZs)** - if one fails, you still work
- **No single point of failure** - 2 NAT Gateways means redundancy

### 💰 Cost Effective
- **Infrastructure as Code** - build same setup in multiple regions easily
- **No overpaying** - only pay for what you use
- **Automatic cleanup** - one command deletes everything

### 🔄 Reproducible
- **Same setup every time** - no accidental differences
- **Easy to version control** - keep code in git, track changes
- **Easy to test changes** - test in dev before prod

