## Numbers & Specs

| Specification | Value | Why? |
|---|---|---|
| **VPC CIDR** | 10.0.0.0/16 | Gives 65,536 IP addresses (plenty) |
| **Public Subnets** | 10.0.1.0/24, 10.0.2.0/24 | 254 IPs each (enough for ALB + NAT) |
| **Private Subnets** | 10.0.10.0/24, 10.0.20.0/24 | 254 IPs each (enough for app servers) |
| **Data Subnets** | 10.0.100.0/24, 10.0.200.0/24 | 254 IPs each (databases) |
| **Availability Zones** | 2 (us-east-2a, us-east-2b) | If one fails, other works |
| **NAT Gateways** | 2 (one per AZ) | High availability (no single point of failure) |
| **Security Groups** | 4 (ALB, App, DB, Bastion) | Least privilege access |
| **Route Tables** | 3 (public, private, data) | Different routing for each tier |
| **VPC Flow Logs** | CloudWatch + S3 | 7-day retention + long-term archive |

